The Deputy Vice Chancellor of Cape Peninsula University of Technology in the Western Cape, says the institution has been working closely with the SRC to ensure they address issues faced by the students. Heidi Giokos has more. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The Cape Peninsula University of Technology is the latest institution to threaten protest action if their demands aren't met. Their concerns are mostly related to student accommodation. The university's SRC claims there are hundreds of students sleeping in corridors. READ: Wits SRC agrees to halt protest for 24 hours But the university insists this isn't the case. The SRC has accused the university of underplaying the situation. eNCA tried to access the areas where its believed students are sleeping but were denied entry.